The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for geometric searching problems, which are typically studied in the computational geometry community. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses probability measures and expected query time, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of decision trees and algebraic decision trees suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of nearest-neighbor queries and numerical methods suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible sub-category.
